name: startup
description: - I learned more about how to resolve merge conflicts. Usually, I do everything through the CLI, which can be a pain, but using the GitLens extension on VSCode made it quite easy to resolve without completely overwriting one of the commits.  - I learned more about how to use SVGs in the Simon HTML assignment. Here are some of the optionsand what they do: M move <to x,y> Q quadratic curve <control point x,y> <to x,y> - I learned how powerful using a framework like Bootstrap really is. I could not have done so much without its help. - I learned that you have so much power over what you are doing, but that means you must be super careful otherwise you code things with little security. - I learned that CSS is the game changer. It can alter EVERYTHING about the web page (aside from the structure).
